						               													<description>In 1998 Rage underwent a major revision that cleaned up a lot of problems with the previous version by White Wolf Studios. Now instead of a free for all the game requires you to watch your resources. Although the backs of the cards have stayed the same the cards now have a lot more info on them and with new rules the original cards are totally incompatible. This is still a game of ferocious werewolf vs. werewolf combat but the game has been changed greatly.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This version is commonly referred to as RALV, Snake Eyes, or Rage: Tribal War to distinguish it from the first version.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If you have cards and are unsure which version they belong to, there's an easy way to tell.  RALV character cards all have a paw print somewhere on the card frame (95% are on the bottom).  Combat cards have a blood spot in the upper left corner with a number in them.  Sept cards list the card type in the upper right corner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
